deck:
Cedbill is a Las Vegas-based writer who dabbles in screenwriting, scripting, playwriting, and poetry. He enjoys long walks on the beach and pretending he lives by a beach upon which he can take long walks. He is also a fond lover of Hanna-Barbera cartoons and big-band swing music.

Ced currently writes PHANTOM SQUAD for Coast Comics.
name: Cedbill

deck: Mandy is a full-time RN on the overnight shifts or as she says, "Saving lives at night and sketching up fantastical ones by day." An avid video game junkie and cyclist, she lives in a world where summer always trumps winter. Mandy is the artist for THE ASTOUNDING AMOEBA ARMADA under Coast Comics.
name: Mandy Marguerite

deck: Jason Russell is a full-time author from New York. His renowned science fiction shorts have finally been compiled into the Kindle book Existent thus forcing him to actually purchase a Kindle. When not creating works of fiction, he balances his scales by writing about mountain biking. Jason is the writer for THE ASTOUNDING AMOEBA ARMADA under Coast Comics.

deck: Alrissa is an artist currently residing in the UK. She loves binge watching TV programs and pretending to know how to take pictures of stuff. She will be studying illustration at NUA this year to get a fancy degree. Alrissa is currently the artist for GONE FISHING under Coast Comics.
name: Alrissa Sia

deck: F.D. is a professional media consumer. He watches Netflix, reads, and goes to the movies religiously. Oh yeah, he also writes. He currently reviews comics at comicsthegathering.com writes GONE FISHING for Coast Comics.
name: F.D. White

deck: Born originally as Gerard Til De Graff, Jerry was born in Holland, Netherlands and is obsessed with anything geeky. Alongside his knowledge in Craft Beer he is a well-versed comic enthusiast. Jerry is one of the co-creators behind WEASELMEIZTERS for Coast Comics.
name: Jerry Choy

deck: Evan was born and raised in not-so-sunny South Florida. A geek through and through, he loves comics, video games, anime/manga, movies, & TV. Currently a grocery store cashier, he is excitedly awaiting the beginning of his writing career. Evan is half of the creative mind behind WEASELMEIZTERS, a title he is co-publishing under Coast Comics.
name: Evan Wucher

deck:
Heralding straight out of Brooklyn, NY, Brentt is an aspiring writer in his mid-twenties building up his portfolio who dabbles in comic books, screenplays, and prose. He enjoys pro wrestling. Sometimes he wanders around aimlessly, too shy to enter restaurants he wants to try.

​Brentt currently acts as lead writer and co-creator of WEASELMEIZTERS.
name: Brentt Harshman

description:
Hi all, Sara here.

I fell in love with graphic novels through Neil Gaiman's Sandman series, but I've always loved to draw. Drawing was an intense interest when I was a kid, and I frequently illustrated stories I wrote or just things I imagined. Drawing was always a way I could communicate things that I was unable to put into words. I am autistic, so I struggled with social interaction, and being able to draw funny little cartoons for classmates gave me a bridge into the social world.

Nowadays, work keeps me from drawing as much as I'd like, but I recently had another comic published in an anthology called 'Simply Sinful' called 'Let's Do Lunch'.
name: Sara Moodie
